When placing a calendar in a column on a page that does not take up the full width of the page, the borders around the days disappear.

To reproduce:

1. Create a two-column layout on a Confluence page
2. Embed a calendar in one of the two columns

This seems to be caused by the following CSS in batch.css, which is overriding the calendar CSS

{code}
table.sectionMacro td {
    border: medium none;
}
{code}

Adding "border=true" to the section macro does appear to resolve this problem, but the CSS conflict should also probably be fixed.

