TeamCalendars offer a dropdown list of timezones that contains erroneous data. For example, "(+0300) Europe/Moscow", while the actual timezone for Moscow is +0400 after DST abolishment in 2011. This happens because TeamCalendars use obsolete TZ database from ical4j, which does not reflect recent changes in timezones, affecting Russia, Belarus, Moldova and other countries.

