The Marketing Team @ Atlassian uses Event Calendars to schedule blog posts on the Atlassian Product Blogs - one Event Calendar per blog, a single event created for each blog post. 

We have a parent page that has all the Event Calendars embedded showing all the scheduled blog posts. There is then a child page for each blog that has a table displaying all the scheduled posts for that blog including a link to the draft in Confluence, a author, and a scheduled publish date.

It would be great to be able to embed the single event for the blog post from the Event Team Calendar in the _Scheduled Publish Date_ field in the table on the child pages.

